SIMPLE: loaded
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: loaded
<hw>loaded</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>containing as much or
as many as is possible; -- of containers, vehicles, trays, etc.; <as>as,
a tray <ex>loaded</ex> with dishes</as></def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> laden.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>containing a shell or an explosive charge ready for
firing; -- of firearms. Opposite of <ant>unloaded</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>charged with associative significance and often
meant to mislead or influence; -- of statements or questions; <as>as, a
<ex>loaded</ex> question</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>having an abundant supply of money or possessions of
value; <as>as, She was not merely rich but
<ex>loaded</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> affluent, flush, moneyed, wealthy.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>very drunk.</def> <mark>[slang]</mark>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> blotto, crocked, fuddled, pissed, pixilated,
plastered, potty, slopped, sloshed, smashed, soused, sozzled, squiffy,
stiff, tiddly, tiddley, tight, tipsy, wet.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Loader</ent>⟦br⟧
